This paper deals with the problem of handling incomplete data in autonomous databases, which is a common issue in database management and information retrieval. The paper proposes a probabilistic approach based on Bayes networks to handle missing attribute values and support query processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach to handle incomplete data. Additionally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper deals with query processing and autonomous data sources.
